Placeholder — the real icon is NOT committed to this repository.
================================================================

The upstream Kiro tarball ships the canonical application icon at:

    Kiro/resources/app/resources/linux/code.png

(i.e. inside the tarball that SRC_URI fetches, at
${WORKDIR}/Kiro/resources/app/resources/linux/code.png after unpack,
or equivalently ${S}/resources/app/resources/linux/code.png with
S="${WORKDIR}/Kiro").

We deliberately do NOT commit a copy of that icon to this git
repository: the upstream Kiro EULA does not clearly grant
redistribution rights for the artwork, and both ebuilds in this
overlay set RESTRICT="strip mirror bindist" specifically because the
binaries are not freely redistributable.

Instead, src_install() in dev-util/kiro-bin/kiro-bin-*.ebuild
installs the icon directly from the unpacked tarball:

    newicon -s 256 "${S}/resources/app/resources/linux/code.png" kiro.png

This file only exists so the presence of dev-util/kiro-bin/files/ is
obvious to a reader of the repository tree, and so the XDG assets
directory is not empty apart from kiro.desktop.

If a future upstream tarball drops the bundled icon, update the
src_install step to extract the icon from whatever path the new
tarball uses, or ewarn and fall back to a generic icon.
